    "body": "### Problem\n\nIn a file with only info or hint diagnostics, the counts are not shown in the statusline.\n\nWhen an error or warn diagnostic is set, all diagnostics are visible in the statusline.\n\nI traced this back to `#vim.diagnostic.count()` (set in 'statusline') that returns 0 even when an info diagnostic count is returned:\n\n```\nlua vim.diagnostic.set(1, 0, { { lnum = 1, severity = \"info\", message = \"info\" } })\nlua =#vim.diagnostic.count() -- Shows 0 ???\nlua =vim.diagnostic.count() -- Shows { [3] = 1 }\nlua =vim.diagnostic.status() -- Shows \"%#DiagnosticSignInfo#I:1%##\" but not shown because of the count predicate in 'statusline'\n```\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```\nnvim --clean\nlua vim.diagnostic.set(1, 0, { { lnum = 1, severity = \"info\", message = \"info\" } })\n-- No diagnostics in statusline.\nlua vim.diagnostic.set(1, 0, { { lnum = 1, severity = \"info\", message = \"info\" }, { lnum = 1, severity = \"error\", message = \"error\" } })\n-- Both error and info counts are shown in statusline.\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nAny diagnostic count is shown in the statusline regardless of severity.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.12.0-dev-2582+g9084483715\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nLinux 6.18.16-200.fc43.x86_64\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.43.1\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nAppImage",
